<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: -6px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Administrative Expenses</U>” means any and all 
expenses incurred by the Company after the APE Filing Date, with respect to 
legal costs related to the proceedings in which the Company participates for the 
purpose of obtaining Court Approval of this Agreement or preserving the 
Company’s assets. Such expenses are entitled to priority in accordance with 
Section 240 of the Bankruptcy Law. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Affiliate</U>” has the meaning specified in 
the Indenture. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Agreement</U>” has the meaning specified in 
the introductory paragraph hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Amount of Unsecured Financial Debt to be 
Restructured</U>” has the meaning specified in Section 2.04 c) hereto. 
</FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>APE</U>” has the meaning specified in the 
introductory paragraph hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>APE Effective Date</U>” has the meaning 
specified in Section 3.01 hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>APE Filing Date</U>” means the date on which 
this Agreement, executed by the majority of creditors required for Court 
Approval, is filed with the Reviewing Court pursuant to Section 72 of the 
Bankruptcy Law, which shall be no later than December 31, 2004. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>APE Solicitation Statement</U>” has the 
meaning specified in the recitals hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Argentina</U>” means the Republic of 
Argentina. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Assets and Liabilities Statement</U>” means 
the list of the Company’s assets and liabilities, as of the Cut-Off Date, as 
certified by an independent public accountant, to be filed with the Reviewing 
Court together with this Agreement, in accordance with the Bankruptcy Law. 
</FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Association</U>” has the meaning specified in 
the introductory paragraph hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Authorizations</U>” has the meaning specified 
in Section 4.05 hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Bank of Italy</U>” means the <I>Banca 
d’Italia.</I> </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Bankruptcy Law</U>” has the meaning specified 
in the recitals hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>BCBA</U>” means the <I>Bolsa de Comercio de 
Buenos Aires</I> or the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>BCRA</U>” means the <I>Banco Central de la 
República Argentina </I>or the Central Bank of the Republic of Argentina. 
</FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px" align=center><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>4 </FONT></P>
<P style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always">
<HR align=center width="100%" color=#999999 SIZE=3>

<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Business Day</U>” means any day on which the 
national courts located in the City of Buenos Aires are open to the public. 
</FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Cash Interest Payments</U>” means, together, 
the Option A/B Cash Interest Payment and the Option C Cash Interest Payment. 
</FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>CER</U>” has the meaning specified in “Certain 
Defined Terms—Terms Relating to the APE Solicitation and Restructuring Plan” of 
the APE Solicitation Statement. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>CNV</U>” means the <I>Comisión Nacional de 
Valores,</I> or the National Securities Commission of Argentina. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Commissions</U>” has the meaning specified in 
the recitals hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Company</U>” has the meaning specified in the 
introductory paragraph hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>CONSOB</U>” means the <I>Commissione Nazionale 
per le Società e la Borsa </I>of Italy, or the Italian Securities and Exchange 
Commission.<B></B> </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Court Approval</U>” has the meaning specified 
in the recitals hereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Creditors’ List</U>” means the list of all of 
the Company’s creditors, as of the Cut-Off Date, as certified by an independent 
public accountant and to be filed with the Reviewing Court together with this 
Agreement, in accordance with the Bankruptcy Law. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Cut-Off Date</U>” means the date as of which 
the Company has prepared the Assets and Liabilities Statement and the Creditors 
List, which shall not be earlier than sixty (60) consecutive days before the APE 
Filing Date. In the event of the Restructuring Without Court Approval, the 
Cut-Off Date will be June 30, 2004. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Dollar</U>” or “<U>US$</U>” means the legal 
currency in the United States of America or any successor currency thereto. 
</FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Effective Date</U>” means the date, as soon as 
practicable, after this Agreement obtains Court Approval, on which the actions 
provided for in Section 7.02 a) hereto will be performed. In the event of the 
Restructuring Without Court Approval, the Effective Date will be such date 
(after the APE Effective Date) on which, as soon as practicable, the actions 
provided for in Section 7.02 a) hereto will be performed. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>Euro</U>” means the single legal currency of 
member states of the European Union, as adopted pursuant to the Maastricht 
Treaty, or any successor thereto. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; TEXT-INDENT: 4%"><FONT 
face="Times New Roman" size=2>“<U>FX Reference Date</U>” means the second New 
York Business Day following the date on which the Company shall have issued a 
press release communicating that it had obtained the requisite legal majorities 
to execute the APE and the level of creditor consent, as provided in the APE 
Solicitation Statement. The Company has publicly announced that the FX Reference 
Date is August 4, 2004. </FONT></P>
<P style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><FONT size=1></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
